  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The dataset provides raw images and corresponding annotation files.",
    "The training set contains 614 positive samples (including 2,416 pedestrians) and 1,218 negative samples.",
    "The test set contains 288 positive samples (including 1,126 pedestrians) and 453 negative samples.The CityPersons dataset is built based on Cityscapes [86].",
    "It was collected from eighteen different cities in Germany, covering three seasons and various weather conditions.",
    "It includes annotations for 35,000 pedestrians in 5,000 images, with an average of 7 instance targets per image.These datasets are valuable resources for pedestrian detection research and have been used in various studies and evaluations related to pedestrian detection algorithms."
